Working with a customer on a performance case, we identified a very slow query which occurred during issue move operations:

{code}SELECT ID, groupid, FIELDTYPE, FIELD, OLDVALUE, OLDSTRING, NEWVALUE, NEWSTRING FROM jiradev.changeitem WHERE (FIELD LIKE ? ) AND (OLDSTRING LIKE ? ) ORDER BY groupid desc{code}

DoS escalation to [~andreask@atlassian.com] resulted in:

{quote}
We should not use a LIKE query when looking up moved issue keys
...
The reason it's a like query and not = is probably mostly historical. I actually wrote part of that code . It was a like already before me... Basically it's never been a performance problem before since we normally don't deal with instances with 900K plus issues. We should fix it now though.
{quote}

Some parts of the quote have been removed by me.

